the meaning of gauge symmetry is

00:51:27.060 --> 00:51:28.980
and the redundancy
encoded in gauge symmetry

00:51:28.980 --> 00:51:30.180
is all something
that you're talking

00:51:30.180 --> 00:51:31.710
about at the order of
the leading order action.

00:51:31.710 --> 00:51:33.750
And you're not talking
about redundancies

00:51:33.750 --> 00:51:35.900
in fields in sub-leading
order, et cetera.

00:51:40.600 --> 00:51:41.100
OK.

00:51:41.100 --> 00:51:42.990
So let's do an
example, now that we

00:51:42.990 --> 00:51:47.580
have this, of how it comes in.

00:51:47.580 --> 00:51:49.170
And I want to come
back to our example

00:51:49.170 --> 00:51:54.170
of our heavy-to-light current
and talk about gauge symmetry

00:51:54.170 --> 00:51:54.670
there.

00:51:59.290 --> 00:52:00.940
If you just took the
tree level result

00:52:00.940 --> 00:52:05.750
that we had in
that case, then we

00:52:05.750 --> 00:52:09.440
had something that just
involved these two guys,

00:52:09.440 --> 00:52:12.800
and this hv field was ultrasoft.

00:52:12.800 --> 00:52:15.170
This guy was collinear.

00:52:15.170 --> 00:52:17.010
So if you did a
Uc transformation,

00:52:17.010 --> 00:52:22.700
then under our rules, what you'd
find is that the cn transforms,

00:52:22.700 --> 00:52:25.670
and this guy doesn't,
the h doesn't.

00:52:25.670 --> 00:52:27.750
So that would not
be gauge invariant.

00:52:39.020 --> 00:52:42.150
But actually, we saw that this
also wasn't the lowest order

00:52:42.150 --> 00:52:42.650
current.

00:52:42.650 --> 00:52:45.350
There was this additional thing,
the Wilson line showed up,

00:52:45.350 --> 00:52:47.660
and that Wilson line is
going to fix this issue.

00:52:47.660 --> 00:52:49.367
It's going to make
it gauge invariant.

00:52:54.240 --> 00:52:56.260
So we have to ask, how
do Wilson lines transform

00:52:56.260 --> 00:52:57.695
under gauge symmetries?

00:53:05.940 --> 00:53:10.390
And that Wilson line
in position space,

00:53:10.390 --> 00:53:13.620
I called it something like this.

00:53:13.620 --> 00:53:15.700
I can't remember if I
used a twiddle or a bar.

00:53:15.700 --> 00:53:18.430
We'll use a bar here for the
position space Wilson line.

00:53:21.070 --> 00:53:24.880
So in general, in just
a regular gauge theory,

00:53:24.880 --> 00:53:28.360
the Wilson line
between two points

00:53:28.360 --> 00:53:31.060
transforms at the endpoints.

00:53:31.060 --> 00:53:32.380
So you get U of x.

00:53:35.710 --> 00:53:37.015
Then, you get a U dagger of y.

00:53:41.340 --> 00:53:43.560
So if you like,
what we would say

00:53:43.560 --> 00:53:46.350
for this Wilson line is that
we have a U of x on one side

00:53:46.350 --> 00:53:48.590
and a U dagger of minus
infinity on the other side.

00:53:57.120 --> 00:54:01.650
Minus infinity is really
long wavelength physics,

00:54:01.650 --> 00:54:03.420
and so we have to
worry a little bit

00:54:03.420 --> 00:54:06.600
about the overlap between
our different types of gauge

00:54:06.600 --> 00:54:09.860
transformations.

00:54:09.860 --> 00:54:13.340
I divided them into three
camps-- collinear, ultrasoft,

00:54:13.340 --> 00:54:18.006
and the global, so let
me do the following.

00:54:29.920 --> 00:54:33.760
To avoid some double counting
with what I called U global,

00:54:33.760 --> 00:54:38.290
let's just simply take,
since U global acts the same

00:54:38.290 --> 00:54:41.950
everywhere, let's just simply
take Uc dagger at minus

00:54:41.950 --> 00:54:44.251
infinity to be 1.

00:54:44.251 --> 00:54:46.810
So this is at some
particular spacetime point.

00:54:46.810 --> 00:54:50.140
We take it to be 1,
and this U global

00:54:50.140 --> 00:54:51.530
will transform at that point.

00:54:51.530 --> 00:54:56.400
We then know there's no overlap
between Uc and U global.

00:54:56.400 --> 00:54:57.930
OK?

00:54:57.930 --> 00:55:01.890
Then, that's enough
to ensure that.

00:55:01.890 --> 00:55:07.290
So with that, our guy under a
collinear gauge transformation

00:55:07.290 --> 00:55:08.700
just transforms on one side.

00:55:12.085 --> 00:55:14.460
If you like, what's happening
is that the coordinate here

00:55:14.460 --> 00:55:17.580
corresponds to this
very large momentum,

00:55:17.580 --> 00:55:22.200
and we're stretching
ourselves out to long distance

00:55:22.200 --> 00:55:25.450
physics which is corresponding
to the smaller momentum.

00:55:25.450 --> 00:55:27.660
So when I think
about transformations

00:55:27.660 --> 00:55:31.170
that should be collinear, I want
them to be associated to the x.

00:55:31.170 --> 00:55:33.420
And I want to associate other
types of transformations

00:55:33.420 --> 00:55:35.190
to what's going on at
infinity which is really

00:55:35.190 --> 00:55:37.857
a spacetime of its own, which is
this ultrasoft spacetime that's

00:55:37.857 --> 00:55:41.680
sitting at the
collinear infinity.

00:55:41.680 --> 00:55:44.318
So that's why I want,
actually, it to look like this.

